  "notes": [
    "UC Santa Cruz students have the option to complete one or more minors, provided they complete all of the required coursework for the minor(s). The sponsoring department establishes the course requirements for a minor. The minor involves substantial work in the discipline and requires no fewer than 25 upper-division or graduate credits. The minor appears on the student's official transcript but not on the diploma. Students do not apply for admission into a minor when applying to UC Santa Cruz. If interested in completing a minor, transfer students must contact the department sponsoring the minor after enrolling at UCSC.",
    "Please visit the department's website to learn more about this minor: https://www.chemistry.ucsc.edu/academics/undergraduates/index.html PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR One of the following chemistry series: CHEM 1A: General Chemistry AND CHEM 1B/1M: General Chemistry and Laboratory AND CHEM 1C/1N: General Chemistry and Laboratory OR CHEM 3A: General Chemistry AND CHEM 3B/3BL: General Chemistry and Lab AND CHEM 3C/3CL: General Chemistry and Lab OR CHEM 4A/4AL: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity and Lab AND CHEM 4B/4BL: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity and Lab as well as the following: CHEM 8A: Organic Chemistry AND CHEM 8L: Organic Chemistry Laboratory CHEM 8B: Organic Chemistry AND CHEM 8M: Organic Chemistry Laboratory One of the following calculus series: MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications AND MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications OR MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics Plus one of the following options: MATH 22: Introduction to Calculus of Several Variables OR MATH 23A: Vector Calculus AND MATH 23B: Vector Calculus OR AM 30: Multivariate Calculus for Engineers Plus one of the following physics sequences: PHYS 6A/6L: Introductory Physics I and Laboratory AND PHYS 6B/6M: Introductory Physics II and Laboratory AND PHYS 6C/6N: Introductory Physics III and Laboratory OR PHYS 5A/5L: Introduction to Physics I and Laboratory AND PHYS 5B/5M: Introduction to Physics II and Laboratory AND PHYS 5C/5N: Introduction to Physics III and Laboratory"
